This new species is similar to 

Gammaphytoptus
machilus

Li, Wei & Wang, 2009, but can be differentiated from the latter by having: the design of prodorsal shield with anterior part covered with striaes (a prodorsal shield design with two rows of cells in 
Gammaphytoptus machilus
); dorsal semiannuli with elliptical microtubercles (dorsal semiannuli smooth in 
Gammaphytoptus machilus
) and ventral semiannuli with elliptical microtubercles (ventral semiannuli with rounded microtubercles in 
Gammaphytoptus machilus
).
